net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator

Class Indicator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator.Indicator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BinaryIndicator, TernaryIndicator, UnaryIndicator

    public abstract class Indicator
extends java.lang.Object
implements net.sf.jclec.IConfigure
    Abstract indicator for measure the quality of the Pareto front. It receives the Pareto set in a list or the file name containing the set. Specific indicators, either unary or binary, are implemented as subclasses.

    Reference book: C.A. Coello, Coello, G.B. Lamont, D.A. Van Veldhuizen, “Evolutionary Algorithms for Solving Multi-Objective Problems”. 2nd Edition. Genetic and Evolutionary Computation Series. Springer. 2007.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
    IConfigure, Serialized Form

      • extractFromFile

        public double[][] extractFromFile(java.lang.String fileName)
        Extract the Pareto front from a file (.txt, .csv). The file should contain a solution in each line, where the objective values must be separated by commas. The name of the objectives can be included as well when using the CSV format.
        Parameters:
        fileName - The name of the file where the Pareto set is stored.
        Returns:
        A matrix of double values that contains the objective values of all the solutions.
